Personnel1.name: Captain Rex
Personnel1.description: Clone Captain Rex served the Republic during the Clone Wars, often taking orders from Anakin Skywalker and Ahsoka Tano

Personnel2.name: Fives
Personnel2.description: Also known as CT-27-5555, Fives trained with Domino Squad on Kamino before being shipped out to the Rishi Moon listening outpost.

Personnel3.name: Echo
Personnel3.description: Echo was a soldier in the Grand Army of the Republic, known for his strict adherence to orders and rules

Personnel4.name: Commander Cody
Personnel4.description: A natural and practical leader in the clone army, Cody was a good fit for General Kenobi, to whom he was particularly loyal.

Personnel5.name: Grand Moff Tarkin
Personnel5.description: As commander of the first Death Star, he proved to be the perfect blend of ruthless, calculating, and arrogant

Personnel6.name: Grand Admiral Thrawn
Personnel6.description: The blue-skinned Chiss was known for his love of art and strategy, and he used the latter to deconstruct his enemies.

Personnel7.name: Orson Krennic
Personnel7.description: Orson rose in the Imperial ranks along with the completion of the Death Star, until his unchecked ambition led to his reckoning on Scarif.

Personnel8.name: General Hux
Personnel8.description: Like most of his ilk, Armitage Hux is ruthless and cunning, and like Tarkin before him, heâ€™s not afraid to stand up to his Force-wielding counterparts
